: "UNSPECIFIED MENTAL DISORDER"}, {"i": 619, "t": "completes"}, {"i": 620, "t": "ICD-10 CODE NOT SPECIFIED"}, {"i": 621, "t": "SYMPTOM DOMAINS OF PRIMARY PSYCHOTIC DISORDERS"}, {"i": 622, "t": "Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder (PMDD)"}, {"i": 623, "t": "PERSONALITY DIFFICULTY"}, {"i": 624, "t": "OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNEA (OSA)"}, {"i": 625, "t": "narcolepsy"}, {"i": 626, "t": "‹ MOOD DISORDERS"}, {"i": 627, "t": "XBT-11"}, {"i": 628, "t": "6A70"}, {"i": 629, "t": "SINGLE EPISODE DEPRESIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 630, "t": "Single Episode Depressive Disorder"}, {"i": 631, "t": "XBT-10"}, {"i": 632, "t": "F32"}, {"i": 633, "t": "SINGLE EPISODE DEPRESIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 634, "t": "DSM-5-TR"}, {"i": 635, "t": "SINGLE EPISODE DEPRESIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 636, "t": "Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 637, "t": "History"}, {"i": 638, "t": "epidemiology"}, {"i": 639, "t": "Etiology and pathogenesis"}, {"i": 640, "t": "clinical picture"}, {"i": 641, "t": "diagnosis"}, {"i": 642, "t": "Examination and assessment"}, {"i": 643, "t": "treatment"}, {"i": 644, "t": "prognosis"}, {"i": 645, "t": "Myths and misconceptions"}, {"i": 646, "t": "Sources"}, {"i": 647, "t": "1. Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 648, "t": "Single episode depressive disorder (ICD-11:"}, {"i": 649, "t": "6A70"}, {"i": 650, "t": "Single Episode Depressive Disorder; DSM-5-TR: Major Depressive Disorder, Single Episode — 296.2x) — an affective disorder causing functional impairment, accompanied by significant cognitive, somatic, and psychomotor symptoms along with depressed mood and/or anhedonia for at least two weeks. Patient's history"}, {"i": 651, "t": "only one"}, {"i": 652, "t": "A major depressive episode is observed (in case of recurrence, code 6A71)."}, {"i": 653, "t": "2. History"}, {"i": 654, "t": "Hippokrat"}, {"i": 655, "t": "— The term \"melancholia\" was used in the 4th century BC."}, {"i": 656, "t": "Kraepelin (1899)"}, {"i": 657, "t": "Depressive episode within manic-depressive insanity."}, {"i": 658, "t": "DSM-III (1980)"}, {"i": 659, "t": "– official diagnosis \"Major Depressive Disorder\"; separation from bipolar disorder."}, {"i": 660, "t": "DSM-5 (2013)"}, {"i": 661, "t": "The \"bereavement exclusion\" (yas istisnası) has been removed — a major depressive episode can be diagnosed in a patient even after the loss of a loved one."}, {"i": 662, "t": "XBT-11 (2019)"}, {"i": 663, "t": "Single episode (6A70) and Repeated (6A71) are coded separately."}, {"i": 664, "t": "3. Epidemiologiya"}, {"i": 665, "t": "Lifetime prevalence: 15–20% (Kessler R.C. NESARC-III, Hasin D.S. et al. JAMA Psychiatry 2018)."}, {"i": 666, "t": "Annual prevalence: ~6–8%."}, {"i": 667, "t": "Sex: 1.5–2 times higher in females."}, {"i": 668, "t": "Onset: mid-20s to 30 years; but possible at any age."}, {"i": 669, "t": "Suicide: depressive disorder associated with ~50% of suicide deaths."}, {"i": 670, "t": "Comorbidity: anxiety disorders 60%, substance use 25%, pain, cardiovascular, diabetes."}, {"i": 671, "t": "Mortality: overall mortality increased 1.5 times (cardiovascular, suicide)."}, {"i": 672, "t": "4. Etiology and pathogenesis"}, {"i": 673, "t": "Heritability 35–40%"}, {"i": 674, "t": "(Sullivan P.F. et al. Am J Psychiatry 2000 meta-analysis); less than bipolar."}, {"i": 675, "t": "GWAS — 100+ risk loci (Howard D.M. et al. Nat Neurosci 2019, n>800,000)."}, {"i": 676, "t": "Neurobiological — monoaminergic (serotonin, norepinephrine, dopamine) hypothesis; HPA axis dysregulation, elevated cortisol; hippocampal volume reduction; inflammatory hypothesis (CRP, IL-6)."}, {"i": 677, "t": "Risk factors:"}, {"i": 678, "t": "childhood trauma, family history, acute stress, chronic medical illness, social isolation, substance use, postpartum period, hypothyroidism."}]